  "text": "Cell States: Drop-Seq Analysis of the Cell Cycle To evaluate the visibility of cell states in Drop-seq, we first examined cell-to-cell variation among the 589 HEK and 412 3T3 STAMPs shown in Figure 3B . Both cultures consisted of asynchronously dividing cells; principal components analysis (PCA) of the single-cell expression profiles showed the top principal components to be dominated by genes with roles in protein Immediately following droplet formation, the cell is lysed and releases its mRNAs, which then hybridize to the primers on the microparticle surface. The droplets are broken by adding a reagent to destabilize the oil-water interface (Experimental Procedures), and the microparticles collected and washed. The mRNAs are then reversetranscribed in bulk, forming STAMPs, and template switching is used to introduce a PCR handle downstream of the synthesized cDNA [CITATION_1] ).",
